               <p>MR. BODKIN conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182812040118"></xptr>GEORGE MIDDLETON. I am in the service of Mr. Griffith, a butcher, of <placeName id="t18281204-236-crimeloc1246">Hampstead</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-236-crimeloc1246" type="placeName" value="Hampstead"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-236-crimeloc1246" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-236-off1244 t18281204-236-crimeloc1246"></join>, and slept in the third-floor - the prisoner lived in the same service, and slept in the room over mine. On the 23d of November, on going to my box, I found it locked as usual, but missed eighteen sovereigns from it - I had no mark on them.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. CLARKSON. Q. How long has he lived there? A. One year and a quarter - three persons slept in my room.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-236-person2038">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  GRIFFITH
               <interp inst="t18281204-236-person2038" type="surname" value="GRIFFITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-236-person2038" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-236-person2038" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner and prosecutor were in my service; the prisoner had 4s. a week - I was present when he was searched, and 6l. 16s. was found on his person, and in his box together - he said his friends had sent it to him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Is he not the son of respectable parents? A. He is.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18281204-236-verdict1247" type="verdictDescription">
